reviews_data.review_text: Very cozy cafe.
Very tasty treats and drinks + excellent ambiance!! Love coming here with my friends :))

Traveling through the area and decided to give this place a try. Wasn't horrible,  but not great.   Chicken salad on croissant was ok... consistency was like it was blended in a food processor. My husband had a sandwich and it was just ok.  Felt it was pricey for what we got.   I will say I had the caramel brownie torte (think that was what it was called).  It was very good. Brownie cheesecake was fair... Basically a small brownie bite with a bit of cream cheese on top. Blueberry peach tart was good.

Lovely place for an afternoon coffee break paired with a delicious dessert. Haven’t had a single bad experience here.

Great place to sit and study. I love to come here and sit upstairs and get schoolwork done. Saved my life in college and continues to be a great place to study in Rock Hill. Highly recommend the macaroons!

reviews_data.review_text: Enjoy an explosive experience on the toilet after an expensive meal.  This place is filthy and run entirely by teens.  Ordered a sandwich with ‘greens’ and instead got an iceberg/cabbage/carrot salad mix on my sandwich— eating slices of thick carrots and red cabbage slivers was disgusting.  Be warned.  Management needs to take over!
We love all Amelie’s in the Charlotte area. We’ve been to all four locations. Today’s visit to the Rock Hill did not disappoint. Our desserts were so yummy!

I visited Amelie’s for the first time and was charmed by the Rock Hill location’s decor and ambiance. The pastries were delicious, and I also enjoyed my half spicy chicken salad and a cup of chicken pot pie soup. The meal was good but not outstanding. I imagine most people visit for the treats more so than the deli offerings, and I certainly enjoyed the sweets more! Service was excellent.

This is a lovely place however the service was terrible. I have a nut allergy. My boyfriend and I ordered pastries which we asked her to keep the nut pastry separate. She gave us attitude when we asked this. We had to ask her to do this twice. The first time she did not place the nut pastry on a separate sheet. I only came here because I was told their coffee was great as I am visiting in town. She was short, glasses with black hair. The second time I was here they specifically asked if we wanted cold or hot beverages and when we indicated hot they gave us a cold drink. To make matters worse. I asked for an additional lid as I saw the woman place her hand over top of the lid already on my cup. When she provided a new lid her hand was over the mouth opening portion of the lid. We were give an espresso shot in a cup with no lid when our order was place “to go”. I’d never come here again. Pastries are the only valuable thing here. Poor customer service, poor food handling. Lastly to add there were flies on the cookies -_-
This place is fabulous!!!

I always need some motivation for the ride; some mornings, enjoying coffee with friends is just the ticket. Amelie's Cafe is always welcoming, offering 5-star service.

Had order delivered, and boy did they deliver!!!
Great pastries, awesome French Italian sandwich!!!
Will visit soon
Wonderful staff, tempting pastries that offer a variety not seen elsewhere, and a charming eclectic atmosphere.
Great little place, good sandwiches and wonderful desserts...
Funky little spot in Rock Hill. Don't be scared off by how small it looks! Plenty of seating upstairs and outside. Everything I've gotten from here is awesome ‼️
Fabulous . Would go again when in town.

reviews_data.review_text: Ordered a turkey sandwich on baguette from Amelie’s this morning. The bread was rock hard and stale. Wouldn’t call it a baguette either. Looks nothing like photos advertised, closest comparison would be ciabatta. The meat was jello-y and low quality, especially considering the price. $13 for a sandwich with old bread and lunchable quality meat is beyond disappointing. A few bites into the 1st half of my sandwich I discovered a hair. Absolutely disgusting. I really wanted to like this place and have been looking forward to trying it, but can’t say I’d recommend. There are better, higher quality options in the area worth spending your money at.
Lots of jobless people still mad at Trump protesting outside, good chai, though.
Such a pretty place. Went here with family & loved the experience. Fun desserts & great food options. Great place to meet up w/ friends & wonderful decorations & atmosphere.
Had a great lunch here. Great food, service, and dog friendly area outside. Loved it.
I came here with some of my friends and the atmosphere was amazing. I got the broccoli cheddar soup which was also amazing. The pastry I got was also pretty good but the texture wasn't for me.

I hate to complain, but that lunch was worst I’ve had in 15 years. Service was too slow to get a couple of bowls of soup taking over 30 minutes?. Soup was lukewarm to cold in texture. Bread was stale. Water tastes like metal and iodine. Horrible experience!!!
Muffins were old. Barista was confusing. Coffee was mediocre. Everything overpriced.
Delicious macarons and pastries!
Very cool restaurant, great eclectic decor, nice staff, and very good food

We stopped by for a quick lunch and space to work, and left with the most delicious pastries! My chicken, pesto, goat cheese sandwich was perfect. Although the soup was a bit lackluster, the service and ambiance made up for it to still allow for a 5-star review. We also got a free macaron because it was our first time! I'm still dreaming about the strawberry cream cheese Danish...

Unfriendly!
My son asked for a milk refill and the cashier responded rudely, saying no free refills and sent him back with his empty cup! For just milk?! Policy is one thing, but kindness costs nothing. Disappointed.
Food is good every visit and the atmosphere of the restaurant is some of my favorite in Rock Hill  it’s a must try especially if you’re visiting the area.
Good food and desserts. Always great service.

reviews_data.review_text:
What a delightful find! An unexpected treasure in an old, converted bank. The double dessert cases are full of beautiful creations- fresh fruit tarts, cakes, eclairs, and a large variety of macroons. My friend and I had not had lunch so opted for the tostines. Great choice!
We shared 2 types- the bacon/fig/cheese (both savory and sweet)
and the savory pesto/tomato/cheese. Both were delicious. We also had a chai and raspberry tea.

There was ample seating both down and upstairs, WIFI and the atmosphere was perfect for our meeting!

I would recommend stopping here if you are looking for a desert and a coffee.  All the deserts looked really good. I got what looked like a custard eclair. The pastry was light and fresh. The custard was delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: I can't understand why I need to be explained over and over again that cappuccino should be in a regular mug. That the mug should have a saucer (if I wanted a pit coffee from a cardboard cup I would go to Starbucks. And every time this happens the employees pour the coffee into the mug, thus getting coffee with milk and not cappuccino) and it's just awful... It puts me off coming back to this place... The cream in the croissants is wrong, they don't know what brie cheese is I don't recommend coming here... Although maybe for this small town it's good, who knows
Delicious tartlets, vanilla eclair and iced coffee.

French eclectic ambiance oozing from every crack in one of the oldest historic building in Rock Hill. Bright, airy, and colorful and right on Main St.  Classic French bistro menu and some of the best pastries you'll find anywhere from Charleston to NYC.
Friendly professional staff serves everyone with a smile. Excellent coffee.  Always plenty of parking.  Great for coffee and a book, or a meeting for lunch with friends or family.  Outside seating.

reviews_data.review_text: We had a blueberry muffin and blueberry bread pudding which scrumptious.  The coffee is amazing! Purchased a bag to take home. French vibes everywhere!🗼🗼

Soups were amazing. French dip was terrible (cheap meat, skimpy). Cleanliness gets 0 stars. Especially the restrooms. They looked like they hadn’t seen a mop in weeks. Dust caked on every picture hanging on the walls. Dining room floors were slightly better looking than the bathroom. I can only imagine what the kitchen looks like…lost my business!

Disappointed to say the least. French dip one single sliver of beef, the dipping broth taste like cup ramen broth! 11.25, felt like an insult. Pastery was good but expensive and tasted old. The black coffee, 12 ounces was cold, we paid 3.50 for that! This was such a let down, do better.

I ordered the French dip and two other pastries. The French dip sucked. Barley any meat, and the sauces tasted like maruchan ramen. I also ordered three coffees. Two tiramisu coffees and one black. It tasted like a quick trip coffee. The pastries were ok. The cheesecake was dry. Service was good though.

Give this cafe a shot. They have many branches and I like this one too. Amazing desert options and a good variety too. Nice options to eat too for food. Overall a great experience and a must try the almond croissant which they might not have at all stores but if you do then please try it.

Try latte options too.
Overall an amazing place to hangout and have a conversation.
I love the eclectic atmosphere, in the midst of a small college town area. Pastries are always on point, and the coffees are perfect.
Great place to enjoy some good pastries and coffee in the afternoon! We are driving from our vacation home in Florida back to Pennsylvania and wanted some good coffee! We were not disappointed!

Rather disappointed. Always used to love going to Amelie’s for their exceptional service, friendly staff, and great drinks. Ordered a cappuccino recently and go the drink below. No foam whatsoever and a very badly pulled espresso shot. Hoping this can be improved.

What’s going on with Amelies??? Everything I order now is just trash!! Old almond croissant every time weird taste of other baked goods they just adding powder sugar on everything now to hide how it really looks and oh my god the baguette is too old even warmed up I could NOT chew it! Also other desserts they mess up the whole menu.. I will never give them a chance anymore…
Maybe the best macaron ever.  Definitely the best in the US.

If I go to Rock Hill for any reason, I always head to Amelie’s for macarons to bring home to my family. They’re definitely not cheap, but what a sweet and special treat! They make me so happy! I will drive from Lancaster all the way over there when I or someone I love is unhappy, just to get that special sweet treat. I wish we had an Amelie’s in Lancaster!

First time visit after finding online.  I mostly went for the macarons, which there were at least a dozen options and some of the largest macarons I've ever seen.  I opted for the French toast and the White chocolate raspberry ones.  In addition, I got a white chocolate mocha flavored coffee.  It was Friday midday on Valentine's Day, so the downstairs dining area was pretty full.  I did see folks going upstairs so I assume there is ample sitting up there as well.  There are a few tables curbside and it appears they have a covered patio sitting area that would be lovely during warmer months.  The menu not only offers sweet delights but also, soup, salad, sandwiches and other savory choices.

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing atmosphere with amazing food.

Stopped in to pick up an assortment of macarons for a bridal shower.
Ben helped me and was very efficient and considerate. He packed  everything very carefully and orderly.
The macarons were a special treat and a hit at the shower. Thank you for all your help and delicious goodies 😊
Just ok today. Sandwich was too dry.

Always a great experience at Amelie’s! I had Jordan helping me! He was very attentive and patient. My daughter was running around so he gave her a macaroon that she absolutely loved! Thank you guys so much for being open! My daughter and I love this bakery sooo much!
Love this location in Rock Hill SC.
I have heard so many great things about this place that I would love to fly over just to taste the atmosphere and see the famous bathroom painting !

Coffee and breakfast was great. Lemon bar and the yogurt and granola were lovely. Such cute eclectic decor. The patio is great when it's not too hot.

Update: the patio is also great when it's chilly, it's closed off with an outdoor heater!

Delicious coffee, pastries, and light meals; exceedingly friendly and personable staff; a terrific atmosphere by yourself to read or to catch up with a group of friends. This place has a large number of regulars, self-included.
Went yesterday with husband and in-laws after dinner. All of the deserts were delicious! Service was great!
Been going to this place for years now and it is a great bakery/pastry spot.
Nice place for dessert and coffee

Such a charming coffee shop. Service is always top-notch.
My daughter spilled water, an employee was on it before I could blink. She brought some extra waters with lids for us!
The coffee and desserts are also great.

Even though it was busy, there was still plenty of seating and it was still relaxing to sit and read a book while drinking a coffee.

Their peppermint mocha (iced) was very tasty and not overly sweet like a certain major coffee chain makes them.

Super cute French Bakery in old Citizens Bank building in downtown Rock Hill SC. Loved the unusual decor..especially the lighting. Don’t forget the locks on the fence outside the restaurant. Just like in Europe
Very pretty and sooo good.

Hi all- it hurts my heart to make this review because I love Amelie’s. I have a friend that is homeless and lives in downtown Rock Hill and sometimes people will buy him food there and he will stay inside to eat. I actually ate there with him one morning after someone else had bought him food. I was surprised to see him there. He said that there was a particular staff member that was giving him a hard time for eating in the restaurant.

I think when money has been exchanged him eating inside shouldn’t be an issue. Regardless someone paid for his food again on another occasion and he was eating inside and the same staff member called the cops on him and had him trespassed. This was over the summer when it was too hot to really be outside. I understand the drive behind these actions but when money has been exchanged he’s a customer. I’d be open to hearing more about this situation from Amelie’s. It seems like a customer was kicked out because he was homeless. I don’t believe he was loitering and I ate breakfast with him and it was peaceful.
Love this charming place. The fruit tart is absolutely delicious. I always get one and a cup of chai tea.  This is one of my go to places to sit and relax and enjoy some yummy treats.

I think this might be my favorite Amélie’s location. I’ve only been twice (so far) but am already looking forward to my next time! It’s the same lovely menu and quirky décor as the other locations but in cute downtown Rock Hill. It was a beautiful day the last time I visited and I enjoyed the front porch area! The staff is always kind, friendly, and helpful when there are too many delicious choices.

reviews_data.review_text: I LOVE the atmosphere here. Their food and pastries are always consistently delicious.
We had a wonderful lunch and coffee here in a little bit of sweets… Highly recommend

I was served a very stale chocolate cake that was so dry at the bottom and throughout that I had to throw it out. I believe it would have been a delicious cake if it were fresh, but that was not my experience. I think I will stick with their main location as I had a fantastic experience with their desserts.
Their pastries are sooo good!! Such a cute shop too
Dear lord this place is magical!! 5+ stars!! Can not wait to go back!! 🤤
A lady came in after me and had two drinks made before mine.
I was only briefly in town, but the food was so amazing I had to get a whole bunch of things to go on my way home. Delicious!
The perfect spot to grab a coffee and dessert downtown. I love the pistachio macaron and salted caramel latte.
Excellent macarons and croissants. Ordered a hot latte and iced latte which were also really good. Nice patio and atmosphere.

Extremely disappointed! We have been to the Charlotte Location and was excited to see one closer to our house.  However,  it was such a disappointment. The food was cold and tasteless. The place was dirty. My coffee came in a to go cup when we specifically said we were staying. Over $200 for meals and to go and desserts and the desserts completely fell apart within our 30 min drive home.
Not all staff was pleasant.
I'll travel to Charlotte next time.

Amelie's Rock Hill was a wonderful place to host a bridal shower.  The room was a perfect size and very private.  Everything was ready when I arrived and beautifully displayed.  The food was delicious.  She even packed up the leftovers for us to take with us.  The staff at Amelie's made this so easy and fun.  Thank you!

LOVE LOVE LOVE. Absolutely gorgeous interior. Feels like im being hugged as soon as I walk in. Instantly reminds you of comfort in France if you have ever been. Food and coffee is delicious i got the quiche lorraine and was to die for 10/10! Recommend for anyone new to the are or just dying for some french cuisine.
There is nothing quite like the pastries at Amelie’s! I felt like an iced coffee & asked the barista to make me his fav, it was divine. Fun atmosphere, friendly staff & delicious menu!!!
shoutout to the girl that made my iced vanilla latte today, it's quite literally the best one I've ever had from here. thank you queen 🫶
Very beautiful inch of French culture in the small rock hill.
The wait staff is amazingly friendly with even better service. Not a bad item to chose from everything is delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: Amelie's

First time to the Rock Hill Main Street area. Nice place to hang out with cute little shops and old town atmosphere. Among several coffee shops we stopped at Amélie’s for a bite and a sweet treat. It was worthy. Appealing to young and not so young with areas to plug in and to relax.  Food was despite the tomato bisque having too much pepper for my taste. Ah! But the desserts…. Worth dying for. I had to take some more to go.  Not to be boomer, but someone should make sure that the silverware is 100% clean.

The aesthetic is quite good, and the staff was quick with our order and friendly.

The food, however, was positively mediocre. Not bad, but absolutely not worth a regular stop. I ordered a croque monsiuer and it came with absolutely stone cold bechemel sauce. My daughter got the kids french toast, which was basically just sticks of dry toast with flavorless syrup.

Amelie's is not awful, there is always something to enjoy about it, but it is positively not worth the price when so many good restaurants are surrounding it.

First time, I'd EVER been to this Rock Hill location!!! I didn't even know they served food FOOD...I thought it was only a coffee and dessert shop!!! EVERYTHING was wonderful and super tasty!! I will deff b bk soon!! 💓💗💕🫶🫶🫶☺️😊😍

What a delightful place!   Quirky yet elegantly decorated.  In an old bank.  Unfortunately there is only 1 person to take your order and it seems like everyone in line had questions.  The food came out pretty quick and was very good.  The bacon was amazing.  The dark roast is pretty strong.  The strawberry something lemonade was really sweet.

I’m really glad we don’t live closer as I would be here all the time trying all the pastries.

The worst excuse for French Toast I have ever had. See the photo I have included. They literally toasted sandwich bread in a toaster (no egg batter was used) and served it with powdered sugar and syrup. Terrible.

I really am not one to write a review but I was really disturbed today. Came here with my two boys. Ordered, sat down to wait on our food and it took 35 mins. We ordered a plain turkey sandwich and a croissant with chicken salad. Everyone was look around for there food waiting just as long as we were. It was busy but nothing crazy. What really bothered me was that the manager I'm assuming was walking around doing inventory!!!!! Not helping her staff. People were waiting FOREVER.  She had no care in the world. Didn't stop what she was doing. Just walking around with a clipboard counting things while her staff were running around. I just don't understand. We could have went to a sit down restaurant and left by the time we got our food there. Also. The food was terrible. The plain sourdough turkey sand had been cut in half and had all kinda of spread all over it from where they cut it I guess.  My son who is so picky didn't want to even eat it. Such I bad experience I will never go back. I wish i had a picture if the food we waited over 30 minutes for.

We always seek out a mom and pop bakery when traveling, that we do often. I had read the reviews and thought that some of the reviews were a bit harsh. To shorten this up a bit we'll start with the positives. Good atmosphere although a little dated. Tables all dirty upon arrival. Pastry window was very appealing. Ordered chicken sandwich and French dip. Chicken sandwich wasn't as spectacular as we expected. The French dip was was delicious. On the way out we picked up a french almond pastry for $6. It was terrible. It was hard like a 3 days old and completely dried out and inedible. Very disappointed. This place may be iconic but it has lost something along the way.
The croissant sandwich okay. The coffee in my cappucino was really nice, but the cappucino itself wasn't made well. Service and atmosphere were great otherwise.
Very busy place. Love all the whimsical art surrounding the tables.
If you have a sweet tooth, this is your place.  The coffee was not bitter.  The breakfast burrito was dry and needed something.  No room for a treat today. I’ll be back many times.

While visiting Rock Hill we were looking for a good local coffee shop. We were so pleased to find Amelie’s French Bakery & Cafe. The selection of baked goods was phenomenal. It was sooo difficult to make up our minds. So we found ourselves getting several selections. Each one was well baked and delicious. The quality was excellent in it all.
They also have a very good tea selection and other cold and hot drinks. My hot latte was made just right.
This location is in an old bank and has a wonderful eclectic atmosphere of decorations and architecture. The old bank vault is very cool!
This will always be a stop for us whenever we are back.
The pastries are awesome, but the brewed coffee is frequently sold cold.

If you need something sweet and delicious you need to visit this place! Our son wanted something sweet so we made a quick stop to see what this place had. After browsing through the options he ordered the chocolate petit gateau. This thing hit the spot and was wonderful!

The drinks haven't been made as well as they used to be. It always seems watered down or something is off. They forget to add things that were paid extra for. And each time I've been coming in, my to-go orders haven't been ready. This happens even when it's not busy. Just seems off nowadays.

Visited this cute eatery today for a snack. I ordered a plain Croissant amd a decaf coffee. Sounds boring, but I was not in the mood for a full meal. As a decaf only drinker, I am used to the worst coffee when I eat at restaurants. This was the best coffee I have had, maybe ever. The server was exceptionally nice, since I must have checked three times that it was actually decaf- only because I’ve been served regular before and my heart nearly exploded 😂.
Always a win-win with Amelie's! Visited for a late afternoon dessert and I just love this place. Had the a slice of the red velvet cheesecake. Delicious!

Delicious spot! Extremely satisfied with everything we ordered: cafe fouetté, cappuccino, chocolate croissants, breakfast wrap, and buttermilk biscuit sandwich. The breakfast wrap was so filling and cooked perfectly. The buttermilk biscuit may be the best biscuit my husband and I have ever had.

Too good for words!!  We didn't make it past the pastries! Next time we will do lunch.  I can't wait to bring my oldest son in here as he lives in Paris and Spain.   Who knew such goodness was in Rock Hill?!!  Simply amazing!  Thank you!!
Best bakery in Rock Hill
Excellent customer service!

Ordered the apple tart. Took one bite. It tasted like medicine. I returned it saying “this is really not good “, the lady took it from me and did not even offer a refund. While waiting for my coffee….I am eating the “chocolate croissant”. Not much of a chocolate inside.
It would have been nice if they called my name when my coffee was ready.

Awful service and the pastry is not good!

Come here if you want to experience being in France 🇫🇷.  Love it. The pastry was amazing.  The Cappuccino and the late were also great.  👌 love to see them having some French accent. All in all they are very friendly.

I hate to have to write a review this low for a place I’ve always loved, but I was so disappointed with this location. Every corner of this café was FILTHY and looked like it hadn’t been cleaned or swept in a year, honestly. I am a true Amelie’s fan and have always gone to the Montford and NoDa ones and been thoroughly impressed, but the Rock Hill location was rough. Although the food and drinks were great, until this place gets a deep clean and stays that way, we likely won’t return here.
The chicken salad sandwich is DELICIOUS!
Cranberry  pecan chicken sanwhich is the best.
Ate lunch here a few months ago with my wife. It was really great. It felt like we were in an incredibly fancy restaurant with prices that were not too bad.
Some of there food were pretty good but another wise that the tables where sticky and they were not clean
Loved my lunch here! Good salad,  and such an array of desserts! Will go back again.

reviews_data.review_text:
Seven people were helped expediently before me. But as soon as I get to the front of the line. I’m standing there waiting for five minutes and no one showed, so I walked out.

One pleasant young lady asked if I wanted anything while I was behind the group. But I didn’t know what macaroons I wanted at the time because I didn’t know the flavors.

I’ll gladly take my business elsewhere.

However, the atmosphere is really nice.
I had the breakfast biscuit with sausage and it was delicious.  It was just really good.
Cappachino was OK. Macaroons were not that good, especially considering the price. Most were hollow. I spent way to much money for the quality of food.

I ordered ahead, arrived early, and they had my latte ready for me! Staff was so friendly and engaging ... even helped me pick out a loaf of fresh cranberry pecan bread. All the treats I got for a holiday get-together were delicious! And the cinnamon palmier that I ate on the way home was perfectly crisp on the outside and soft inside ... delicious!! Thank you!!
Great place to relax and have lunch, or get some work done on your laptop.

I love the fig bacon and brie tartine! I crave it everyday non stop. Desserts are good too but sometimes the crusts are pretty hard and I would not recommend the bread pudding. When I got it a couple times ago it was cold in the middle and hard on the outside. The drinks aren’t the best either but I liked the pumpkin chai. My boyfriend likes the croissants. A little on the pricey side but the atmosphere makes up for it.

Great experience! I go here very often and it’s always delicious. Their desserts are great! They make everything fresh to order and everything is highly customizable! Great atmosphere and everyone is friendly. Would highly recommend!
Dress warm, this lovely shop is not temperature friendly for its guests.
Thanks for being amazing, especially during a busy Saturday lunch rush! For my first time at this location, I will have to say it is my new favorite.
Forget it.

We stopped by on our visit to the arcade nearby — we’ve never been to Rock Hill before. Having already walked by Rock Hill coffee shop, we stopped there first and grabbed some iced coffees. Upon entering Amelie, we were greeted nicely and went to order brunch. However, as we were ordering we were told that if we wanted to drink our iced coffees we would have to eat outside. In other words, we were not allowed to eat inside this cafe (which unbeknownst to us, also serves coffee) if we wanted to continue drinking our iced coffee from the roaster right down the road. We asked them if they were sure they didn’t want to take our money, and the cashier informed us that they were sorry but they didn’t make the rules. Rather than be shamed into eating outside on a warm day, we took our business next door to Flipside cafe right down the road. They were great and happily welcomed us and our iced coffees.
Chicken Pesto Goat Cheese sandwich was good; the chicken slightly dry. The French dip was also good, but light on the roast beef. The breads for each was outstanding.

All Amelie's coffee shops have something in common, but every location is unique. This one is my favorite so far. Creatively decorated, with taste and humor. It's always nice to sit down and enjoy good coffee from a real ceramic cup. The staff is personable and welcoming, the whole atmosphere has a cozy small town vibe.

This place is AMAZING! Everything is absolutely delicious and affordable! We only spent about $15 per person! I’ve been here for lunch and desserts twice now, and both times it was phenomenal! I love their sandwiches, soups, and salads! The éclairs are so good! The vanilla cream inside was very creamy and had great flavor. Their tartlets are delicious and come in many varieties, including my favorite: lemon raspberry. Their crème brûlée is the best I’ve ever had, and the coffee is very good as well. The best way to sum it up, is I told them they needed to open one up in Chattanooga, TN, where I'm from. They really deserve more than 5 stars.

Wonderful selection of gluten free products with knowledgeable staff. Even new staff members knew immediately where to find gluten free listing of products when she was unsure. Always change gloves and box separately. It’s as close as you can get to gluten free considering it’s a shared kitchen and I feel they take great care to offer the best experience possible.
I love this place. Excellent coffee and bakery!

This place is so much fun! Awesome coffee, the baguette was the best I've ever had. My daughter got macarons & I got an eclair for my husband. Sat outside & pretended we were in France! I just wish they had vegan treats!!
Excelentes los crousants y muy buen servicio!!
Best macarons! The entire menu is delicious!
Great customer service and tasty treats!
Delicious treats!

The food and coffee here were wonderful! I loved my lavender flavor added to dark roast brew...so good! The bakery items were very tasty and the staff very friendly. Indoors was decorated with a unique style and they even had a miniature Pont des Arts outside on the railing! I will definitely be back...my mom and I enjoyed our stop for a midweek birthday brunch!
Very disappointed at the Rock Hill location.  Macarons were definitely not fresh. Crust was just hard. I'll stick with NoDa.
Really enjoyed the coffee and sweet treats. Visited after a volleyball tournament at the Rock Hill Center.
Never disappointed! Best macarons around! Great service and fair pricing considering the quality product you receive.
I Eat a Macarons and Tarts. It's that is good
Delicious pastries, coffee and breakfast sandwiches. We went out of our way to stop.
Yummy

Absolutely delicious! They have a lot of choices to choose from! The only thing I could say to make it the best place in the area, would be to add vegan desserts to the mix. Such as no egg or dairy at all . If you're wondering whether you should go I definitely recommend it!
I always enjoy this place.
Amazing as always, best pastries in Rockhill by far.
Love it! I had mouse topped with a chocolate covered strawberry. It was awesome.
The latte Chain tea recommended😉😊💛💙❤

reviews_data.review_text: Enjoy an explosive experience on the toilet after an expensive meal.  This place is filthy and run entirely by teens.  Ordered a sandwich with ‘greens’ and instead got an iceberg/cabbage/carrot salad mix on my sandwich— eating slices of thick carrots and red cabbage slivers was disgusting.  Be warned.  Management needs to take over!
We love all Amelie’s in the Charlotte area. We’ve been to all four locations. Today’s visit to the Rock Hill did not disappoint. Our desserts were so yummy!

I visited Amelie’s for the first time and was charmed by the Rock Hill location’s decor and ambiance. The pastries were delicious, and I also enjoyed my half spicy chicken salad and a cup of chicken pot pie soup. The meal was good but not outstanding. I imagine most people visit for the treats more so than the deli offerings, and I certainly enjoyed the sweets more! Service was excellent.

This is a lovely place however the service was terrible. I have a nut allergy. My boyfriend and I ordered pastries which we asked her to keep the nut pastry separate. She gave us attitude when we asked this. We had to ask her to do this twice. The first time she did not place the nut pastry on a separate sheet. I only came here because I was told their coffee was great as I am visiting in town. She was short, glasses with black hair. The second time I was here they specifically asked if we wanted cold or hot beverages and when we indicated hot they gave us a cold drink. To make matters worse. I asked for an additional lid as I saw the woman place her hand over top of the lid already on my cup. When she provided a new lid her hand was over the mouth opening portion of the lid. We were give an espresso shot in a cup with no lid when our order was place “to go”. I’d never come here again. Pastries are the only valuable thing here. Poor customer service, poor food handling. Lastly to add there were flies on the cookies -_-
This place is fabulous!!!

Had order delivered, and boy did they deliver!!!

Will visit soon

Great little place, good sandwiches and wonderful desserts...

Fabulous . Would go again when in town.

reviews_data.review_text: Ordered a turkey sandwich on baguette from Amelie’s this morning. The bread was rock hard and stale. Wouldn’t call it a baguette either. Looks nothing like photos advertised, closest comparison would be ciabatta. The meat was jello-y and low quality, especially considering the price. $13 for a sandwich with old bread and lunchable quality meat is beyond disappointing. A few bites into the 1st half of my sandwich I discovered a hair. Absolutely disgusting. I really wanted to like this place and have been looking forward to trying it, but can’t say I’d recommend. There are better, higher quality options in the area worth spending your money at.
Lots of jobless people still mad at Trump protesting outside, good chai, though.
Such a pretty place. Went here with family & loved the experience. Fun desserts & great food options. Great place to meet up w/ friends & wonderful decorations & atmosphere.
Had a great lunch here. Great food, service, and dog friendly area outside. Loved it.
I came here with some of my friends and the atmosphere was amazing. I got the broccoli cheddar soup which was also amazing. The pastry I got was also pretty good but the texture wasn't for me.

I hate to complain, but that lunch was worst I’ve had in 15 years. Service was too slow to get a couple of bowls of soup taking over 30 minutes?. Soup was lukewarm to cold in texture. Bread was stale. Water tastes like metal and iodine. Horrible experience!!!
Muffins were old. Barista was confusing. Coffee was mediocre. Everything overpriced.
Delicious macarons and pastries!
Very cool restaurant, great eclectic decor, nice staff, and very good food

We stopped by for a quick lunch and space to work, and left with the most delicious pastries! My chicken, pesto, goat cheese sandwich was perfect. Although the soup was a bit lackluster, the service and ambiance made up for it to still allow for a 5-star review. We also got a free macaron because it was our first time! I'm still dreaming about the strawberry cream cheese Danish...

Unfriendly!
My son asked for a milk refill and the cashier responded rudely, saying no free refills and sent him back with his empty cup! For just milk?! Policy is one thing, but kindness costs nothing. Disappointed.
Food is good every visit and the atmosphere of the restaurant is some of my favorite in Rock Hill  it’s a must try especially if you’re visiting the area.
Good food and desserts. Always great service.

reviews_data.review_text:
What a delightful find! An unexpected treasure in an old, converted bank. The double dessert cases are full of beautiful creations- fresh fruit tarts, cakes, eclairs, and a large variety of macroons. My friend and I had not had lunch so opted for the tostines. Great choice!
We shared 2 types- the bacon/fig/cheese (both savory and sweet)
and the savory pesto/tomato/cheese. Both were delicious. We also had a chai and raspberry tea.

There was ample seating both down and upstairs, WIFI and the atmosphere was perfect for our meeting!

I would recommend stopping here if you are looking for a desert and a coffee.  All the deserts looked really good. I got what looked like a custard eclair. The pastry was light and fresh. The custard was delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: I can't understand why I need to be explained over and over again that cappuccino should be in a regular mug. That the mug should have a saucer (if I wanted a pit coffee from a cardboard cup I would go to Starbucks. And every time this happens the employees pour the coffee into the mug, thus getting coffee with milk and not cappuccino) and it's just awful... It puts me off coming back to this place... The cream in the croissants is wrong, they don't know what brie cheese is I don't recommend coming here... Although maybe for this small town it's good, who knows
Delicious tartlets, vanilla eclair and iced coffee.

French eclectic ambiance oozing from every crack in one of the oldest historic building in Rock Hill. Bright, airy, and colorful and right on Main St.  Classic French bistro menu and some of the best pastries you'll find anywhere from Charleston to NYC.
Friendly professional staff serves everyone with a smile. Excellent coffee.  Always plenty of parking.  Great for coffee and a book, or a meeting for lunch with friends or family.  Outside seating.

reviews_data.review_text: We had a blueberry muffin and blueberry bread pudding which scrumptious.  The coffee is amazing! Purchased a bag to take home. French vibes everywhere!🗼🗼

Soups were amazing. French dip was terrible (cheap meat, skimpy). Cleanliness gets 0 stars. Especially the restrooms. They looked like they hadn’t seen a mop in weeks. Dust caked on every picture hanging on the walls. Dining room floors were slightly better looking than the bathroom. I can only imagine what the kitchen looks like…lost my business!

Disappointed to say the least. French dip one single sliver of beef, the dipping broth taste like cup ramen broth! 11.25, felt like an insult. Pastery was good but expensive and tasted old. The black coffee, 12 ounces was cold, we paid 3.50 for that! This was such a let down, do better.

I ordered the French dip and two other pastries. The French dip sucked. Barley any meat, and the sauces tasted like maruchan ramen. I also ordered three coffees. Two tiramisu coffees and one black. It tasted like a quick trip coffee. The pastries were ok. The cheesecake was dry. Service was good though.

Give this cafe a shot. They have many branches and I like this one too. Amazing desert options and a good variety too. Nice options to eat too for food. Overall a great experience and a must try the almond croissant which they might not have at all stores but if you do then please try it.

Try latte options too.
Overall an amazing place to hangout and have a conversation.
I love the eclectic atmosphere, in the midst of a small college town area. Pastries are always on point, and the coffees are perfect.
Great place to enjoy some good pastries and coffee in the afternoon! We are driving from our vacation home in Florida back to Pennsylvania and wanted some good coffee! We were not disappointed!

Rather disappointed. Always used to love going to Amelie’s for their exceptional service, friendly staff, and great drinks. Ordered a cappuccino recently and go the drink below. No foam whatsoever and a very badly pulled espresso shot. Hoping this can be improved.

What’s going on with Amelies??? Everything I order now is just trash!! Old almond croissant every time weird taste of other baked goods they just adding powder sugar on everything now to hide how it really looks and oh my god the baguette is too old even warmed up I could NOT chew it! Also other desserts they mess up the whole menu.. I will never give them a chance anymore…
Maybe the best macaron ever.  Definitely the best in the US.

If I go to Rock Hill for any reason, I always head to Amelie’s for macarons to bring home to my family. They’re definitely not cheap, but what a sweet and special treat! They make me so happy! I will drive from Lancaster all the way over there when I or someone I love is unhappy, just to get that special sweet treat. I wish we had an Amelie’s in Lancaster!

First time visit after finding online.  I mostly went for the macarons, which there were at least a dozen options and some of the largest macarons I've ever seen.  I opted for the French toast and the White chocolate raspberry ones.  In addition, I got a white chocolate mocha flavored coffee.  It was Friday midday on Valentine's Day, so the downstairs dining area was pretty full.  I did see folks going upstairs so I assume there is ample sitting up there as well.  There are a few tables curbside and it appears they have a covered patio sitting area that would be lovely during warmer months.  The menu not only offers sweet delights but also, soup, salad, sandwiches and other savory choices.

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing atmosphere with amazing food.

Stopped in to pick up an assortment of macarons for a bridal shower.
Ben helped me and was very efficient and considerate. He packed  everything very carefully and orderly.
The macarons were a special treat and a hit at the shower. Thank you for all your help and delicious goodies 😊
Just ok today. Sandwich was too dry.

Always a great experience at Amelie’s! I had Jordan helping me! He was very attentive and patient. My daughter was running around so he gave her a macaroon that she absolutely loved! Thank you guys so much for being open! My daughter and I love this bakery sooo much!
Love this location in Rock Hill SC.
I have heard so many great things about this place that I would love to fly over just to taste the atmosphere and see the famous bathroom painting !

Coffee and breakfast was great. Lemon bar and the yogurt and granola were lovely. Such cute eclectic decor. The patio is great when it's not too hot.

Update: the patio is also great when it's chilly, it's closed off with an outdoor heater!

Delicious coffee, pastries, and light meals; exceedingly friendly and personable staff; a terrific atmosphere by yourself to read or to catch up with a group of friends. This place has a large number of regulars, self-included.
Went yesterday with husband and in-laws after dinner. All of the deserts were delicious! Service was great!
Been going to this place for years now and it is a great bakery/pastry spot.
Nice place for dessert and coffee

Such a charming coffee shop. Service is always top-notch.
My daughter spilled water, an employee was on it before I could blink. She brought some extra waters with lids for us!
The coffee and desserts are also great.

Even though it was busy, there was still plenty of seating and it was still relaxing to sit and read a book while drinking a coffee.

Their peppermint mocha (iced) was very tasty and not overly sweet like a certain major coffee chain makes them.

Super cute French Bakery in old Citizens Bank building in downtown Rock Hill SC. Loved the unusual decor..especially the lighting. Don’t forget the locks on the fence outside the restaurant. Just like in Europe
Very pretty and sooo good.

Hi all- it hurts my heart to make this review because I love Amelie’s. I have a friend that is homeless and lives in downtown Rock Hill and sometimes people will buy him food there and he will stay inside to eat. I actually ate there with him one morning after someone else had bought him food. I was surprised to see him there. He said that there was a particular staff member that was giving him a hard time for eating in the restaurant.

I think when money has been exchanged him eating inside shouldn’t be an issue. Regardless someone paid for his food again on another occasion and he was eating inside and the same staff member called the cops on him and had him trespassed. This was over the summer when it was too hot to really be outside. I understand the drive behind these actions but when money has been exchanged he’s a customer. I’d be open to hearing more about this situation from Amelie’s. It seems like a customer was kicked out because he was homeless. I don’t believe he was loitering and I ate breakfast with him and it was peaceful.
Love this charming place. The fruit tart is absolutely delicious. I always get one and a cup of chai tea.  This is one of my go to places to sit and relax and enjoy some yummy treats.

I think this might be my favorite Amélie’s location. I’ve only been twice (so far) but am already looking forward to my next time! It’s the same lovely menu and quirky décor as the other locations but in cute downtown Rock Hill. It was a beautiful day the last time I visited and I enjoyed the front porch area! The staff is always kind, friendly, and helpful when there are too many delicious choices.

I was served a very stale chocolate cake that was so dry at the bottom and throughout that I had to throw it out. I believe it would have been a delicious cake if it were fresh, but that was not my experience. I think I will stick with their main location as I had a fantastic experience with their desserts.
Their pastries are sooo good!! Such a cute shop too
Dear lord this place is magical!! 5+ stars!! Can not wait to go back!! 🤤
A lady came in after me and had two drinks made before mine.
I was only briefly in town, but the food was so amazing I had to get a whole bunch of things to go on my way home. Delicious!
The perfect spot to grab a coffee and dessert downtown. I love the pistachio macaron and salted caramel latte.
Excellent macarons and croissants. Ordered a hot latte and iced latte which were also really good. Nice patio and atmosphere.

Extremely disappointed! We have been to the Charlotte Location and was excited to see one closer to our house.  However,  it was such a disappointment. The food was cold and tasteless. The place was dirty. My coffee came in a to go cup when we specifically said we were staying. Over $200 for meals and to go and desserts and the desserts completely fell apart within our 30 min drive home.
Not all staff was pleasant.
I'll travel to Charlotte next time.

Amelie's Rock Hill was a wonderful place to host a bridal shower.  The room was a perfect size and very private.  Everything was ready when I arrived and beautifully displayed.  The food was delicious.  She even packed up the leftovers for us to take with us.  The staff at Amelie's made this so easy and fun.  Thank you!

LOVE LOVE LOVE. Absolutely gorgeous interior. Feels like im being hugged as soon as I walk in. Instantly reminds you of comfort in France if you have ever been. Food and coffee is delicious i got the quiche lorraine and was to die for 10/10! Recommend for anyone new to the are or just dying for some french cuisine.
There is nothing quite like the pastries at Amelie’s! I felt like an iced coffee & asked the barista to make me his fav, it was divine. Fun atmosphere, friendly staff & delicious menu!!!
shoutout to the girl that made my iced vanilla latte today, it's quite literally the best one I've ever had from here. thank you queen 🫶
Very beautiful inch of French culture in the small rock hill.
The wait staff is amazingly friendly with even better service. Not a bad item to chose from everything is delicious.

reviews_data.review_text: Amelie's

First time to the Rock Hill Main Street area. Nice place to hang out with cute little shops and old town atmosphere. Among several coffee shops we stopped at Amélie’s for a bite and a sweet treat. It was worthy. Appealing to young and not so young with areas to plug in and to relax.  Food was despite the tomato bisque having too much pepper for my taste. Ah! But the desserts…. Worth dying for. I had to take some more to go.  Not to be boomer, but someone should make sure that the silverware is 100% clean.

The aesthetic is quite good, and the staff was quick with our order and friendly.

The food, however, was positively mediocre. Not bad, but absolutely not worth a regular stop. I ordered a croque monsiuer and it came with absolutely stone cold bechemel sauce. My daughter got the kids french toast, which was basically just sticks of dry toast with flavorless syrup.

Amelie's is not awful, there is always something to enjoy about it, but it is positively not worth the price when so many good restaurants are surrounding it.

First time, I'd EVER been to this Rock Hill location!!! I didn't even know they served food FOOD...I thought it was only a coffee and dessert shop!!! EVERYTHING was wonderful and super tasty!! I will deff b bk soon!! 💓💗💕🫶🫶🫶☺️😊😍

What a delightful place!   Quirky yet elegantly decorated.  In an old bank.  Unfortunately there is only 1 person to take your order and it seems like everyone in line had questions.  The food came out pretty quick and was very good.  The bacon was amazing.  The dark roast is pretty strong.  The strawberry something lemonade was really sweet.

I’m really glad we don’t live closer as I would be here all the time trying all the pastries.

The worst excuse for French Toast I have ever had. See the photo I have included. They literally toasted sandwich bread in a toaster (no egg batter was used) and served it with powdered sugar and syrup. Terrible.

I really am not one to write a review but I was really disturbed today. Came here with my two boys. Ordered, sat down to wait on our food and it took 35 mins. We ordered a plain turkey sandwich and a croissant with chicken salad. Everyone was look around for there food waiting just as long as we were. It was busy but nothing crazy. What really bothered me was that the manager I'm assuming was walking around doing inventory!!!!! Not helping her staff. People were waiting FOREVER.  She had no care in the world. Didn't stop what she was doing. Just walking around with a clipboard counting things while her staff were running around. I just don't understand. We could have went to a sit down restaurant and left by the time we got our food there. Also. The food was terrible. The plain sourdough turkey sand had been cut in half and had all kinda of spread all over it from where they cut it I guess.  My son who is so picky didn't want to even eat it. Such I bad experience I will never go back. I wish i had a picture if the food we waited over 30 minutes for.

We always seek out a mom and pop bakery when traveling, that we do often. I had read the reviews and thought that some of the reviews were a bit harsh. To shorten this up a bit we'll start with the positives. Good atmosphere although a little dated. Tables all dirty upon arrival. Pastry window was very appealing. Ordered chicken sandwich and French dip. Chicken sandwich wasn't as spectacular as we expected. The French dip was was delicious. On the way out we picked up a french almond pastry for $6. It was terrible. It was hard like a 3 days old and completely dried out and inedible. Very disappointed. This place may be iconic but it has lost something along the way.
The croissant sandwich okay. The coffee in my cappucino was really nice, but the cappucino itself wasn't made well. Service and atmosphere were great otherwise.
Very busy place. Love all the whimsical art surrounding the tables.
If you have a sweet tooth, this is your place.  The coffee was not bitter.  The breakfast burrito was dry and needed something.  No room for a treat today. I’ll be back many times.

While visiting Rock Hill we were looking for a good local coffee shop. We were so pleased to find Amelie’s French Bakery & Cafe. The selection of baked goods was phenomenal. It was sooo difficult to make up our minds. So we found ourselves getting several selections. Each one was well baked and delicious. The quality was excellent in it all.
They also have a very good tea selection and other cold and hot drinks. My hot latte was made just right.
This location is in an old bank and has a wonderful eclectic atmosphere of decorations and architecture. The old bank vault is very cool!
This will always be a stop for us whenever we are back.
The pastries are awesome, but the brewed coffee is frequently sold cold.

If you need something sweet and delicious you need to visit this place! Our son wanted something sweet so we made a quick stop to see what this place had. After browsing through the options he ordered the chocolate petit gateau. This thing hit the spot and was wonderful!

The drinks haven't been made as well as they used to be. It always seems watered down or something is off. They forget to add things that were paid extra for. And each time I've been coming in, my to-go orders haven't been ready. This happens even when it's not busy. Just seems off nowadays.

Visited this cute eatery today for a snack. I ordered a plain Croissant amd a decaf coffee. Sounds boring, but I was not in the mood for a full meal. As a decaf only drinker, I am used to the worst coffee when I eat at restaurants. This was the best coffee I have had, maybe ever. The server was exceptionally nice, since I must have checked three times that it was actually decaf- only because I’ve been served regular before and my heart nearly exploded 😂.
Always a win-win with Amelie's! Visited for a late afternoon dessert and I just love this place. Had the a slice of the red velvet cheesecake. Delicious!

Delicious spot! Extremely satisfied with everything we ordered: cafe fouetté, cappuccino, chocolate croissants, breakfast wrap, and buttermilk biscuit sandwich. The breakfast wrap was so filling and cooked perfectly. The buttermilk biscuit may be the best biscuit my husband and I have ever had.

Too good for words!!  We didn't make it past the pastries! Next time we will do lunch.  I can't wait to bring my oldest son in here as he lives in Paris and Spain.   Who knew such goodness was in Rock Hill?!!  Simply amazing!  Thank you!!
Best bakery in Rock Hill
Excellent customer service!

Ordered the apple tart. Took one bite. It tasted like medicine. I returned it saying “this is really not good “, the lady took it from me and did not even offer a refund. While waiting for my coffee….I am eating the “chocolate croissant”. Not much of a chocolate inside.
It would have been nice if they called my name when my coffee was ready.

Awful service and the pastry is not good!

Come here if you want to experience being in France 🇫🇷.  Love it. The pastry was amazing.  The Cappuccino and the late were also great.  👌 love to see them having some French accent. All in all they are very friendly.

I hate to have to write a review this low for a place I’ve always loved, but I was so disappointed with this location. Every corner of this café was FILTHY and looked like it hadn’t been cleaned or swept in a year, honestly. I am a true Amelie’s fan and have always gone to the Montford and NoDa ones and been thoroughly impressed, but the Rock Hill location was rough. Although the food and drinks were great, until this place gets a deep clean and stays that way, we likely won’t return here.
The chicken salad sandwich is DELICIOUS!
Cranberry  pecan chicken sanwhich is the best.
Ate lunch here a few months ago with my wife. It was really great. It felt like we were in an incredibly fancy restaurant with prices that were not too bad.
Some of there food were pretty good but another wise that the tables where sticky and they were not clean
Loved my lunch here! Good salad,  and such an array of desserts! Will go back again.

reviews_data.review_text:
Seven people were helped expediently before me. But as soon as I get to the front of the line. I’m standing there waiting for five minutes and no one showed, so I walked out.

One pleasant young lady asked if I wanted anything while I was behind the group. But I didn’t know what macaroons I wanted at the time because I didn’t know the flavors.

I’ll gladly take my business elsewhere.

However, the atmosphere is really nice.
I had the breakfast biscuit with sausage and it was delicious.  It was just really good.
Cappachino was OK. Macaroons were not that good, especially considering the price. Most were hollow. I spent way to much money for the quality of food.

I ordered ahead, arrived early, and they had my latte ready for me! Staff was so friendly and engaging ... even helped me pick out a loaf of fresh cranberry pecan bread. All the treats I got for a holiday get-together were delicious! And the cinnamon palmier that I ate on the way home was perfectly crisp on the outside and soft inside ... delicious!! Thank you!!
Great place to relax and have lunch, or get some work done on your laptop.

I love the fig bacon and brie tartine! I crave it everyday non stop. Desserts are good too but sometimes the crusts are pretty hard and I would not recommend the bread pudding. If you haven't been to Amelie's yet, then you need to get it in gear and go. I ate at two of their locations and both were WONDERFUL!!! I'm a French Cuisine freak, so I am highly critical of French Restaurants, Bakeries, Cafes and Bistros. You can't go wrong with Amelia's. The food is GENUINELY French and oh, so, so, good. The girls at The Rock Hill location could have been more friendly and hospitable, but perhaps they were just having one of those not so good mornings, we all have. BUT. It sure didn't come out in the food. Everything was made to perfection. If I had more time in the area, I would have been back for more. This is definitely a must go to French Bakery and Restaurant. The Croque Monsieur was great. As all of the other items I had. And you can't walk out without any kind of the bakery items or you will be missing even more good items. The pastries and the small mousse cups never made it to lunch hour. I will most definitely be back for more of Amelie's. The best way to sum it up, is I told them they needed to open one up in Chattanooga, TN, where I'm from. They really deserve more than 5 stars.
